### Please check if the PR fulfills these requirements:

This is a split PR of #7435, adding the gradeable type. 

### What is the current behavior?
Currently, the externally hosted repositories are student created/student provided .

### What is the new behavior?
This adds a new externally hosted VCS type, where the professor provides the URL, and creates the repositories that students fork. 
![image](https://github.com/Submitty/Submitty/assets/46759635/90862506-8c01-43d2-8e84-9a40b06bcc52)
__
![image](https://github.com/Submitty/Submitty/assets/46759635/b1fb777c-19b1-4e74-8a47-d1285e108216)

## Other Information
The way 'we' use it, is to have the VCS base url be the SSH url to the gitlab/github repository, but with {$user_id} instead of the instructor's user id. (e.g. git@github.com:{$user_id}/cptr141.git) When students fork this repository, it changes to their user id. To use this, the students GIT id has has to be the same as their user_id in Submitty.

### Please check if the PR fulfills these requirements:

* [ ] Tests for the changes have been added/updated (if possible)
* [ ] Documentation has been updated/added if relevant ## TODO

The second split of PR  #7435 , adding support for subdirectories.

### What is the current behavior?

Currently every gradeable (if using VCS), has to be in a separate repository. 

Also, the current subdirectory variable is not actually subdirectories, so it has been refactored to vcs_partial_path. 

### What is the new behavior?
This PR adds a new parameter in the New Gradeable page for if the gradeable is in a subdirectory of the main repository. 
![image](https://github.com/Submitty/Submitty/assets/46759635/0167a300-4ef1-484d-ac7d-e718f0504f28)

### Other information?
This will break currently created gradeables, however new gradeables created after this is merged will not (hopefully) break. 

Tests have been added for the autograding_shipper portion, not the website/php portion.

### Please check if the PR fulfills these requirements:
closes part of #9380 

### What is the current behavior?
Currently if the repository for a VCS gradeable is empty, either no files get checked out, or a failure text file is put in the checkout path. The name of this text file is the only error message that occurs when something goes wrong with submitting files.

### What is the new behavior?
If no files are submitted (with a repository that allows empty commits) it shows 
![image](https://github.com/Submitty/Submitty/assets/46759635/9b0aa691-35ca-4030-89cd-451083cacb3c)
If a 'failure' text file is found., it displays the 'tips' found in the failure text file.

![image](https://github.com/Submitty/Submitty/assets/46759635/4a698ea2-190f-4d17-95fd-af510109d87e)

### Please check if the PR fulfills these requirements:

* [ ] Tests for the changes have been added/updated (if possible)
* [ ] Documentation has been updated/added if relevant

### What is the current behavior?
Currently there doesn't exist a sample gradeable where students submit by committing files to a version control system (VCS) repository.

### What is the new behavior?
This PR adds such a gradeable with sample submissions, to help with development and future testing of the feature.

### Other information?
The current state of the PR:
- A gradeable (with autograding) is created with the under the right settings
- The repositories that belong to the gradeable for all the users in the course are generated succesfully
- Sample files are committed to the students' repos

#9399 was merged, and if the user selects 'do not grade this assignment', a site error would show with 'count must be used on an array'
![image](https://github.com/Submitty/Submitty/assets/46759635/dc75e9c9-e5ce-4884-a797-7ef78f634525)


### What is the new behavior?
This is now fixed

pr_body:
### What is the current behavior?
Setup sample courses.py file currently has hardcoded form.json variables, this causes the form files to be different from the config files passed in from the .yml files.

### What is the new behavior?
The form.json files have been updated to take the current values of the gradeable, instead of hardcoded values. 

This fixes the difference between the form.json config, and the parameters set by the .yml file, 

This also fixes an issue where the subdirectories weren't properly being utilized in the sample courses.

### What is the current behavior?

I missed an instance of that function, so there are errors in the autograding of zip submissions.

### Please check if the PR fulfills these requirements:

* [x] Documentation has been updated/added if relevant  [Documentation pull request](https://github.com/Submitty/submitty.github.io/pull/517)

### What is the current behavior?
Submitty has been using selenium to test features for a while, but it has been getting overtaken in popularity and use-cases by Cypress. Selenium tests have also been a source of frustration with flaky tests. 

### What is the new behavior?
Since all of the tests that were running in CI using Selenium have been re-written in Cypress, the Selenium job has been removed from the CI workflow, and some of the files that have already been re-written have been deleted. 

### Other information?
There are still some tests written in selenium that haven't been running in CI, these will need to be assessed to determine if it is worth re-writing them in cypress, or just deleting them and writing completely new tests.

### What is the current behavior?
We currently have no YAML validation.  This can lead to improper YAML being introduced into our codebase as seen in https://github.com/Submitty/Submitty/pull/8788.  

### What is the new behavior?
This PR adds the [yamllint](https://yamllint.readthedocs.io/en/stable) tool to validate our YAML files automatically.  In practice, this will mostly help validate GitHub Actions workflow files, the dependabot configuration file, and the files which define the sample courses.

All of our existing failures have been addressed in this PR to make the linter pass successfully.

An associated documentation PR will be forthcoming soon.

pr_title: [Testing:Developer] Change cypress login to post request
pr_body:
### What is the current behavior?
Currently the cypress login function logs in manually using the UI at the /authentication/login page, and the logout function clicks the logout button on the sidebar. 

### What is the new behavior?
Cypress uses a POST request to manually login and logout without using the UI. 
see https://docs.cypress.io/guides/references/best-practices#Organizing-Tests-Logging-In-Controlling-State
and  https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5XQOK0v_YRE

### Other information?
After this is merged, it would be good to remove all of the `cy.visit('/')` instances that happen just before a `cy.login()`, as they are now obsolete.

A line has been added to the sidebar tests to catch the server errors that still allow the page to be viewed.

pr_body:
### What is the current behavior?
Currently we just use the testing component of cypress.

### What is the new behavior?
This will add the setup to have cypress link with cypress cloud, which will allow for easier parallelization, and it shows recordings of the tests in the cloud. 

### Other information?
~~The open source license allows for 100,000 runs (specific it('', ()=>{})  functions, not spec files) per month, so this is the testing period to see if this is enough, if not, it may be better to manually parallelize the tests and use cloud as a different feature, to see why cypress is failing in CI and not locally, but we will see. I have also communicated with some people at cypress, and they indicated that we may be able to get more runs, but I haven't communicated more about that.~~

This information is old. We now have an OSS cypress cloud 'organization', which allows for unlimited runs, not 100,000/month.
